<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title"><strong>PUERTO RICO POSTPONES DEBT PLAN</strong> <span class="divider"> | </span></span> Puerto Rico <b>delayed its plan for a negotiated moratorium on $72 billion of debt</b> by a week, citing time lost because of a tropical storm, <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2015/08/31/business/dealbook/puerto-rico-postpones-debt-plan.html?ref=dealbook">Mary Williams Walsh reports in DealBook</a>. </p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Officials have been working on the plan since Gov. Alejandro GarcÃ­a Padilla announced  in June that the island would never be able to repay its debt without profound structural changes. The plan was  <b>due to be completed by Sunday</b> but on Saturday evening the governorâs chief of staff, VÃ­ctor SuÃ¡rez MelÃ©ndez, said it was not ready.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">âThe governmentâs efforts in the past days have been focused on preparing for the possible impact of Tropical Storm Erika,â he said in a news release.  <b>The new due date is Sept. 8.</b></p>
